so this is the form, I want to ask you how can I add a calculation to the total if user selects rush, the total gets doubled or x2. How can I do that?

Yes, here's another way using custom JavaScript:

1. In your WordPress admin panel, go to "Forms" and then click on your laundry order form to edit it.
2. Click on the "Settings" tab and then select "Custom CSS & JS" from the left sidebar menu. (If you don’t see the "Custom CSS & JS" option, you may need to install the free Gravity Forms Custom CSS & Javascript plugin. You can download it [here](https://wordpress.org/plugins/custom-css-js-plugin/#description)).
3. Copy the following custom JavaScript code and paste it into the "Custom Javascript" text area:

```javascript
jQuery(document).ready(function($) {
  function updateTotal() {
    var deliveryType = $("input[name=input_11]:checked").val();
    var multiplier = deliveryType === "Express" ? 2 : 1;

    var productIds = [16, 17, 18, 20, 19];
    var total = 0;

    for (var i = 0; i < productIds.length; i++) {
      var currentPrice = parseFloat($("input[name='input_" + productIds[i] + ".2']").val());
      var currentQuantity = parseInt($("input[name='ginput_quantity_" + productIds[i] + "']").val() || 0);
      total += currentPrice * currentQuantity;
    }

    total *= multiplier;
    $("input[name='input_21']").val(total.toFixed(2)).trigger('change');
  }

  $("input[name=input_11]").on("change", updateTotal);
  $(".ginput_quantity").on("change", updateTotal);  
});
```

4. Save your form.

With this code, when the user selects the "Express" option in the "Delivery Type" field, the total will be doubled. This code adds event listeners to the "Delivery Type" radio buttons and quantity fields, and when any of these fields change, it calculates the total by considering the doubled price for the Express option.

Note: Make sure you have jQuery included in your WordPress theme, as this custom script relies on it.

